    <annotation>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="head">
                    <marginalia_text>A deep, &amp; profound politique, no way possible, to be vndermined, or pumped dry, of sounded to the depth.</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia anchor_text="Syphax" hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>Numidaru[m] Rex: de quo multa Liuius.</marginalia_text>
                    <book title="Ab Urbe Condita"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The king of the Numidians: much about whom in Livy.</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>Secrecy, on of [the] souerainest Rules, of Vegetius Rules: &amp; therfore more then once, of twise
                        repeatid, in that breife sententious chapter.
                  </marginalia_text>
                    <book title="De re Militari"/>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="270" place="left_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>Fons omniu[m] Strategematu[m], secretus, et intricatus procedendi modus, multis Technarum ambagibus implicitus.
                        Nam simplicia Strategemata rarò succedunt: Composita,
                        ipsos maximè fallentes, fallu[n]t maximè. Vulpis pera, dolis referta.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The source of all stratagems: a secret and complex way of proceeding, obscured by many ambiguities of 
            cunning tricks. For simple stratagems rarely succeed: composite ones deceive them greatly, they deceive greatly. The bag of the fox, stuffed with tricks. </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
                    <marginalia_text>Malo nodo, malus qua[e]rendus Cuneus.</marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref book_title="Epistles" language="LA" person="Jerome" text="Malo nodo, malus quaerendus cuneus."/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>"For a bad knot, a bad wedge must be found."</translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
                    <marginalia_text>Eueryman reddy to interteine intelligence, &amp; to mainteine discourse: but how few
                    meet, to reteine counsel, or to conceale matters of Secrecy?</marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
